BP is dropping very quickly.

27
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,708
I know. Can you hold that for me?

28
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,250
Please step aside.

29
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:30,708
Stand over there.

30
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:33,333
Doctor, allow me to raise the table up.

31
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:35,791
Great.

32
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:37,750
Apply suction here.

33
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:39,166
How's the bleeding?

34
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:40,333
Still heavy.

35
00:03:40,958 --> 00:03:42,250
Apply swab and sponge.

36
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:43,916
Cut here.

37
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,125
How's the BP?

38
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,166
BP is much better.

39
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,791
I think the bleeding is under control.

40
00:03:50,791 --> 00:03:52,000
Check the BP again.

41
00:03:52,083 --> 00:03:54,250
BP is great, 120/70.

42
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,416
Cut please.

43
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,041
You can take it from here.

44
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:01,083
Can you manage?

45
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:28,041
Cautery may not always
be a better option than sutures.

46
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,458
You have to check the bleeding.
Whether it's from the vein or the artery.

47
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:36,083
-Yes.
-These cases are rare but possible.

48
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:40,583
So you should be prepared.
Think and decide much faster.

49
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:43,541
Don't just stand around
and wait for a miracle to happen.

50
00:04:45,666 --> 00:04:47,333
I wasn't waiting for a miracle.

51
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:52,250
I was trying to stop the bleeding,
I thought it was going to stop.

52
00:04:57,375 --> 00:04:59,583
Don't stress yourself out.

53
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:01,416
You're still a resident.

54
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:03,625
I'm stressed

55
00:05:04,583 --> 00:05:06,416
because you said
I was waiting for a miracle.

56
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:09,333
I don't want you to get the wrong idea.

57
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,000
Why?

58
00:05:13,125 --> 00:05:14,708
What's so bad about a miracle?

59
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:16,625
Nothing.

60
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:20,166
But people who wait for miracles,

61
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,791
they have already lost
by believing in them.

62
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:41,375
You're hardworking.

63
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:45,333
I'm looking into the last patient's file.

64
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,208
I have to study it carefully,

65
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:50,333
so I can succeed in the future.

66
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,833
You've got an attitude.

67
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:56,541
That's why things
got tense with Dr. Thana.

68
00:05:59,958 --> 00:06:01,916
How did you know about it so soon?

69
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:04,958
Well, Dr. Panthana

70
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:08,750
is on the most wanted list
of all the girls in this hospital.

71
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:10,666
How could I not know?

72
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:13,541
He's handsome, that's true.

73
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,750
But aren't the girls
afraid of his unfriendliness?

74
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:19,208
Bee, he's like that

75
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,375
because he's sad.

76
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:22,791
Sad?

77
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:26,083
You don't know?

78
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:27,750
Where have you been?

79
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,708
His case is very famous.

80
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:31,583
What happened?

81
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,500
Two years ago...

82
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,666
Dr. Thana's story is very famous
on the Internet.

83
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,125
HERE IT IS AGAIN,
A BOUQUET OF WHITE ROSES.

84
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:40,625
Everybody's been talking
about Dr. White Roses.

85
00:06:40,875 --> 00:06:42,375
Mysterious white roses on the toll way.

86
00:06:42,458 --> 00:06:43,541
I have seen them too for two months now.

87
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:44,916
They say...

88
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,541
The flowers are for the dead.

89
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:48,375
Really? That's scary.

90
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:50,750
What's the real story?
Can somebody tell us?

91
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,166
The tale of the roses
that went viral over the Internet.

92
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:04,416
There was an accident here,
a man and a woman, both are doctors.

93
00:07:04,916 --> 00:07:06,083
They were going to get married

94
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:08,041
in just a week
before the accident happened.

95
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:10,875
They drove the car, then boom!
The woman died, but the guy survived.

96
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:17,958
He must have loved her very much.
He brings her flowers every Sunday night.

97
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,166
Can you give us an interview?

98
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:29,666
