Then that means you haven't forgiven me.

268
00:29:30,333 --> 00:29:35,750
How about this, I'll take you home
to make up for what I said.

269
00:29:37,708 --> 00:29:39,500
I have to go with you, right?

270
00:29:41,208 --> 00:29:43,208
Get in, we're blocking the road.

271
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:00,791
Are you hungry?

272
00:30:02,416 --> 00:30:03,875
Let's go eat first.

273
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:06,583
I'd rather not.

274
00:30:07,333 --> 00:30:08,958
I need to go to this place.

275
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:12,458
Could you accompany me there?

276
00:30:12,833 --> 00:30:13,833
Please?

277
00:30:23,833 --> 00:30:24,916
Thank you.

278
00:30:29,166 --> 00:30:31,166
I thought we were going to eat.

279
00:30:31,791 --> 00:30:33,291
You're only having coffee.

280
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:36,250
I only meant to come to this place.

281
00:30:38,125 --> 00:30:39,666
Come to this place?

282
00:30:41,083 --> 00:30:42,333
What do you mean?

283
00:30:44,458 --> 00:30:47,375
For the last two years,

284
00:30:47,458 --> 00:30:48,750
I visit this place once a year.

285
00:30:50,083 --> 00:30:51,333
Two years?

286
00:30:52,583 --> 00:30:53,750
Once a year?

287
00:30:54,666 --> 00:30:57,000
This restaurant is very important to me.

288
00:31:29,750 --> 00:31:32,166
You haven't eaten?

289
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:34,625
I told you not to wait for me.

290
00:31:36,083 --> 00:31:38,083
Today was such a chaotic day.

291
00:31:38,375 --> 00:31:40,083
My cell phone is totally dead.

292
00:31:40,916 --> 00:31:42,291
So what you did was--

293
00:31:42,375 --> 00:31:45,416
I left you a message, of course.

294
00:31:45,541 --> 00:31:46,708
I know how meticulous you are.

295
00:31:49,791 --> 00:31:51,541
There were some problems with the case.

296
00:31:51,708 --> 00:31:53,833
I almost didn't make it out.

297
00:31:53,916 --> 00:31:57,208
One of the nurses said that
we're lucky there's a miracle.

298
00:31:57,333 --> 00:31:58,416
So you said--

299
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:00,375
So I had to lecture her for a bit.

300
00:32:00,458 --> 00:32:03,958
We have knowledge and technology.

301
00:32:04,041 --> 00:32:06,750
We have everything.
Do we have to rely on miracles?

302
00:32:07,541 --> 00:32:08,791
People believe in such things.

303
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,833
I'm sorry, I've been complaining.

304
00:32:17,625 --> 00:32:18,833
Let it all out.

305
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:20,791
It will then be my turn.

306
00:32:22,333 --> 00:32:23,541
Is something wrong?

307
00:32:36,250 --> 00:32:37,125
Nok.

308
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:41,416
It's fine if you don't believe me.

309
00:32:44,958 --> 00:32:46,291
But you're my miracle.

310
00:33:15,083 --> 00:33:16,416
This binds us together.

311
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,125
From now on,

312
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:22,291
wherever you go,

313
00:33:23,250 --> 00:33:24,333
I'll follow you.

314
00:33:26,833 --> 00:33:28,416
When you feel down,

315
00:33:29,208 --> 00:33:30,625
I'll be next to you.

316
00:33:32,541 --> 00:33:33,958
When you're happy,

317
00:33:35,125 --> 00:33:36,583
I'll be in front of you.

318
00:33:38,833 --> 00:33:41,500
But when you feel sad,

319
00:33:41,583 --> 00:33:43,291
I'll be right behind you.

320
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,541
I will do my best to take care of you.

321
00:33:56,583 --> 00:33:57,833
I promise.

322
00:33:59,458 --> 00:34:01,375
Well, it looks like it's not just binding.

323
00:34:01,458 --> 00:34:03,208
We're going to be stuck together.

324
00:34:04,416 --> 00:34:06,416
If you let me go, I'll be so mad at you.

325
00:34:08,375 --> 00:34:09,666
I'll never let you go.

326
00:34:23,541 --> 00:34:26,541
I sat here waiting for Nok,

327
00:34:26,625 --> 00:34:28,208
for three hours...

328
00:34:31,958 --> 00:34:33,541
but I was so happy.

329
00:34:39,416 --> 00:34:42,041
After that day,

330
00:34:42,125 --> 00:34:43,791
I sit here alone at this table.

331
00:34:47,166 --> 00:34:48,291
And this...

332
00:34:49,625 --> 00:34:50,625
has tortured me.

333
00:34:59,833 --> 00:35:01,125
I think...

334
00:35:01,916 --> 00:35:03,666
this is a nice place.

335
00:35:07,541 --> 00:35:09,250
But you might get bored
if you come too often.

336
00:35:12,750 --> 00:35:15,541
It's like the love between you and Nok.

337
00:35:22,333 --> 00:35:26,083
I'm not trying to be intrusive,

338
00:35:26,166 --> 00:35:31,833
but from what I've been hearing
from you and other people,

339
00:35:31,916 --> 00:35:34,750
I think Nok wouldn't
want you to stay like this.

340
00:35:37,666 --> 00:35:40,166
You think Nok would want me to forget her?

341
00:35:47,041 --> 00:35:50,708
We hold on to the moments
that made us happy, right?

342
00:35:55,666 --> 00:35:58,541
If we only try to hold on
to the happy moments,

343
00:35:58,625 --> 00:36:00,958
isn't it harder to let go of the pain?

344
00:36:46,541 --> 00:36:48,166
Thank you for your advice.

345
00:36:54,833 --> 00:36:59,000
Excuse me, sir.
Could you please move your car?

346
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:00,916
It seems that your car wasn't in neutral.

347
00:37:41,625 --> 00:37:43,541
NOK
UNKNOWN NUMBER

348
00:37:54,416 --> 00:37:56,166
Thana, look at it this way,

349
00:37:56,500 --> 00:37:59,833
the later I am,
the more I'll be missing you.

350
00:38:00,375 --> 00:38:01,541
Hold on...

351
00:38:01,625 --> 00:38:03,041
I'll come to you soon.

352
00:38:48,458 --> 00:38:50,000
Thank you for dropping me off at home.

353
00:38:50,625 --> 00:38:52,708
I'm the one who should thank you.

354
00:38:52,791 --> 00:38:55,125
I was holding on to the happy memories.

355
00:38:55,208 --> 00:38:57,291
And that makes it harder to let go.

356
00:39:01,916 --> 00:39:03,833
What if I try to be happy again?

357
00:39:05,125 --> 00:39:07,791
Do I have to prepare myself
for another heartache?

358
00:39:49,458 --> 00:39:50,833
Hello, Mom.

359
00:40:08,416 --> 00:40:09,708
Who was that?

360
00:40:10,416 --> 00:40:15,250
And you pretend like
you're watching some Korean series.

361
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:19,166
Spying on you is much more fun
than any Korean series.

362
00:40:20,833 --> 00:40:21,958
He's a colleague.

363
00:40:22,625 --> 00:40:24,625
He's just a colleague for now.

364
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:28,666
It seems like it's going to stay that way.

365
00:40:28,750 --> 00:40:30,958
Why? Does he already have a girlfriend?

366
00:40:32,291 --> 00:40:33,333
He did.

367
00:40:34,083 --> 00:40:36,041
Are you sure it's in the past?

368
00:40:40,583 --> 00:40:43,000
Either way, it has nothing to do with me.

369
00:40:44,208 --> 00:40:46,666
In any case, just be careful.

370
00:40:46,791 --> 00:40:49,333
I don't want you to be involved
with someone else's boyfriend.

371
00:40:49,416 --> 00:40:50,541
Or you'll be miserable like me.

372
00:40:50,625 --> 00:40:52,958
Oh, Mom.

373
00:40:53,708 --> 00:40:57,666
His girlfriend might
come looking for you at home.

374
00:41:19,833 --> 00:41:24,541
Sorry, I know it's late,

375
00:41:24,625 --> 00:41:27,333
but I need this for tomorrow.

376
00:41:27,500 --> 00:41:28,833
No problem. Come by in the morning.

377
00:41:28,916 --> 00:41:31,250
-Thank you, sorry for the trouble.
-It's okay.

378
00:41:57,375 --> 00:41:59,000
Thank you for accompanying me.

379
00:41:59,333 --> 00:42:01,458
Thank you for your words of advice.

380
00:42:06,041 --> 00:42:08,291
Thank you, too,
for dropping me off at home.

381
00:42:14,541 --> 00:42:15,791
Sweet dreams.

382
00:42:40,250 --> 00:42:41,541
You too.

383
00:44:41,208 --> 00:44:43,583
Hey!

384
00:44:44,166 --> 00:44:47,333
You look exhausted,
did you get enough sleep?

385
00:44:49,416 --> 00:44:50,625
Or...

386
00:44:50,958 --> 00:44:52,666
the ghost of Dr. Nok visited you?

387
00:44:54,583 --> 00:44:56,250
Why did you...

388
00:44:56,916 --> 00:44:59,083
I'm just kidding.

389
00:44:59,833 --> 00:45:03,250
Yesterday, I saw you get in the car
with Dr. Thana, right?

390
00:45:03,625 --> 00:45:06,791
If I were Dr. Nok, I'd be jealous.

391
00:45:07,958 --> 00:45:09,708
That is nonsense, June.

392
00:45:10,083 --> 00:45:12,791
I just accompanied him.

393
00:45:13,166 --> 00:45:16,333
It's fine if you two
are going to be more than colleagues.

394
00:45:17,291 --> 00:45:18,583
I'm going.

395
00:45:24,458 --> 00:45:25,541
How are you today?

396
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:28,125
Not bad.

397
00:45:28,750 --> 00:45:30,541
Where's your boyfriend?

398
00:45:32,208 --> 00:45:35,541
He's not here, he's watching
a football match with friends.

399
00:45:39,833 --> 00:45:41,208
Happy birthday.

400
00:45:42,958 --> 00:45:44,166
Thank you.

401
00:45:48,541 --> 00:45:49,916
Let me see your wound.

402
00:45:56,208 --> 00:45:57,583
Even on my birthday!

403
00:45:58,458 --> 00:45:59,958
Men are always like this.

404
00:46:01,041 --> 00:46:03,291
He said the flirting part was his duty.

405
00:46:03,625 --> 00:46:05,583
Now that we're together, it's my duty.

406
00:46:06,958 --> 00:46:08,875
How did Dr. Thana's girlfriend do it?

407
00:46:12,916 --> 00:46:17,000
She isn't with him anymore,
but he still loves her.

408
00:46:17,958 --> 00:46:20,666
You're being too serious.
You're still young.

409
00:46:21,583 --> 00:46:22,708
Dr. Bee.

410
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:25,333
If you and Dr. Thana were together,

411
00:46:25,458 --> 00:46:28,166
what would you do
to make him love only you?

412
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:33,250
If Dr. Thana liked me
and we were together,

413
00:46:33,333 --> 00:46:35,708
that would mean
he's no longer in love with his ex.

414
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:39,583
I thought you said
you wanted to meet decent guys.

415
00:46:39,666 --> 00:46:42,500
Well, then, that doesn't count,
she's dead.

416
00:46:47,458 --> 00:46:48,541
Get some rest.

417
00:47:21,708 --> 00:47:25,291
Are you sure it's a good idea
for a doctor to smoke?

418
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:29,500
-Does the smell bother you?
-No, it's fine.

419
00:47:30,625 --> 00:47:32,500
I like the smell of cigarettes.

420
00:47:34,416 --> 00:47:36,500
The smell reminds me of my dad.

421
00:47:40,250 --> 00:47:41,583
Nok didn't like it.

422
00:47:42,583 --> 00:47:44,291
So I had to sneak up here a lot.

423
00:47:48,333 --> 00:47:51,500
But you still brought her along.

424
00:48:05,083 --> 00:48:06,291
What are you listening to?

425
00:48:06,958 --> 00:48:07,958
What?

426
00:48:08,666 --> 00:48:10,166
What are you listening to?

427
00:48:19,708 --> 00:48:22,250
It's my favorite song
that I always listen to.

428
00:48:22,708 --> 00:48:25,750
When I'm tired or discouraged
and I listen to this song,

429
00:48:25,833 --> 00:48:27,458
I feel like...

430
00:48:27,708 --> 00:48:29,583
I have some support.

431
00:49:09,958 --> 00:49:11,250
I like her.

432
00:49:12,375 --> 00:49:13,583
What about you?

433
00:51:34,375 --> 00:51:35,458
Were you dreaming?

434
00:51:38,791 --> 00:51:40,000
Sorry.

435
00:52:33,958 --> 00:52:37,375
Dr. Nok, I'm sorry. I won't do it again.

436
00:54:18,666 --> 00:54:20,500
What are you two doing?

437
00:54:26,375 --> 00:54:27,958
What the hell are you doing?

438
00:54:30,166 --> 00:54:32,250
You scared the shit outta me! So scary!

439
00:54:33,333 --> 00:54:34,458
Happy birthday!

440
00:54:35,666 --> 00:54:37,875
Love you, miss you.

441
00:55:59,958 --> 00:56:01,416
What's wrong, Dr. Bee?

442
00:56:03,083 --> 00:56:04,125
Nang.

443
00:56:13,416 --> 00:56:15,250
Dr. Nok? Really?

444
00:56:15,916 --> 00:56:17,291
That's very unlikely.

445
00:56:17,666 --> 00:56:19,708
You think I'm seeing things?

446
00:56:20,750 --> 00:56:23,041
No, I didn't mean it like that.

447
00:56:23,833 --> 00:56:26,375
It's just that Dr. Nok
was a really nice person.

448
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:30,666
Even if she was a ghost,
she wouldn't be a mean one.

449
00:56:35,875 --> 00:56:37,416
I've never seen her myself.

450
00:56:39,958 --> 00:56:41,875
They said that...

451
00:56:42,958 --> 00:56:46,791
she came to haunt those
who flirted with Dr. Thana.

452
00:56:50,666 --> 00:56:54,041
I'm not saying that you flirted with him.

453
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:58,333
But he does flirt with you.

454
00:57:01,458 --> 00:57:03,250
He flirts with me?

455
00:57:04,666 --> 00:57:06,125
It's true.

456
00:57:07,041 --> 00:57:11,708
Ever since you came to train here,

457
00:57:11,791 --> 00:57:13,833
he seems to be in a better mood.

458
00:57:14,416 --> 00:57:15,875
He smiles more often.

459
00:57:17,333 --> 00:57:18,583
I doubt that.

460
00:57:19,041 --> 00:57:21,041
A guy like Dr. Thana likes me?

461
00:57:23,916 --> 00:57:25,250
But I hope he does.

462
00:57:28,375 --> 00:57:31,166
If he really does like you,

463
00:57:31,708 --> 00:57:34,000
will you like him back?

464
00:57:38,916 --> 00:57:42,208
I'm not considering
anything more than that.

465
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:45,666
I just want to help him
get over his grief.

466
00:57:47,916 --> 00:57:49,041
Really?

467
01:00:52,250 --> 01:00:55,583
I saw you standing there awhile,
what have you been doing?

468
01:01:03,916 --> 01:01:05,958
Dr. Nok? Really?

469
01:01:06,458 --> 01:01:08,041
That's very unlikely.

470
01:01:08,208 --> 01:01:10,291
You think I'm seeing things?

471
01:01:11,500 --> 01:01:14,000
No, I didn't mean it like that.

472
01:01:14,375 --> 01:01:16,958
It's just that Dr. Nok
was a really nice person.

473
01:01:17,458 --> 01:01:20,041
Even if she was a ghost,
she wouldn't be a mean one.

474
01:01:22,791 --> 01:01:24,708
They said that...

475
01:01:25,875 --> 01:01:29,625
she came to haunt those
who flirted with Dr. Thana.

476
01:01:35,666 --> 01:01:38,750
No. I'm not saying
that you flirt with him.

477
01:01:39,458 --> 01:01:42,333
But he does flirt with you.

478
01:01:43,041 --> 01:01:45,458
Earlier you said that...

479
01:01:47,083 --> 01:01:48,875
Dr. Thana flirts with me.

480
01:01:50,250 --> 01:01:51,541
It's true.

481
01:01:51,958 --> 01:01:55,208
Ever since you came to train here,

482
01:01:56,125 --> 01:01:58,416
he seems to be in a better mood.

483
01:01:59,625 --> 01:02:01,458
He smiles more often.

484
01:02:05,583 --> 01:02:07,500
But I hope he likes you.

485
01:02:09,166 --> 01:02:11,958
If he really does like you,

486
01:02:12,750 --> 01:02:14,666
will you like him back?

487
01:02:20,375 --> 01:02:21,875
I've never thought about that.

488
01:02:24,250 --> 01:02:25,458
Really?

489
01:02:28,541 --> 01:02:32,166
Well, you should,
so he could get over his grief.

490
01:02:53,083 --> 01:02:53,916
Dr. Thana.

491
01:02:54,000 --> 01:02:55,416
The patient is a Thai woman aged 31.

492
01:02:55,500 --> 01:02:57,916
She was in an accident,
her car crashed into a lamp post.

493
01:02:58,000 --> 01:03:00,458
Her breathing is 30 per BP 70/30.

494
01:03:00,750 --> 01:03:02,416
I think she has pneumothorax.

495
01:03:02,500 --> 01:03:03,625
Give me number 32.

496
01:03:03,708 --> 01:03:05,291
ICD number 32.

497
01:03:06,750 --> 01:03:08,125
Scalpel number 10.

498
01:03:15,500 --> 01:03:16,666
Thana!

499
01:03:21,916 --> 01:03:23,208
Find Dr. Prapon.

500
01:03:47,583 --> 01:03:51,750
I think we were lucky
that there wasn't any significant loss.

501
01:03:53,333 --> 01:03:57,958
However, this mistake cannot be ignored.

502
01:03:58,666 --> 01:04:01,000
So the committee and I,

503
01:04:02,166 --> 01:04:06,208
we have agreed that you should refrain
from performing surgery temporarily.

504
01:04:15,333 --> 01:04:16,875
About last night...

505
01:04:19,333 --> 01:04:21,000
Seeing the patient last night

506
01:04:21,083 --> 01:04:23,875
might have reminded him
of the night that Nok died.

507
01:04:24,250 --> 01:04:26,291
The cases are very similar.

508
01:04:26,750 --> 01:04:28,333
The patient was also a woman.

509
01:04:29,666 --> 01:04:30,750
Is that all?

510
01:04:31,041 --> 01:04:32,291
He probably felt guilty.

511
01:04:33,416 --> 01:04:34,708
He felt guilty?

512
01:04:35,958 --> 01:04:37,791
He probably felt guilty about Dr. Nok.

513
01:04:41,958 --> 01:04:43,958
Can you wait for me on the 14th floor?

514
01:04:44,041 --> 01:04:45,916
-I'll see you there.
-Yes, Doctor.

515
01:04:46,666 --> 01:04:48,791
-Bee.
-Yes.

516
01:04:49,166 --> 01:04:51,000
Did you hear that Thana resigned?

517
01:04:52,583 --> 01:04:53,791
He resigned?

518
01:04:53,875 --> 01:04:57,125
Yes. He submitted a resignation
letter, but Dr. Sanchai refused.

519
01:04:57,500 --> 01:04:59,291
He told Thana to reconsider.

520
01:05:00,291 --> 01:05:01,958
So where is he now?

521
01:05:02,583 --> 01:05:04,125
I don't know.

522
01:05:06,666 --> 01:05:08,750
If you can find him,

523
01:05:08,833 --> 01:05:11,958
tell him to go talk to Dr. Sanchai
or Dr. Prapon.

524
01:05:13,458 --> 01:05:15,416
-Okay.
-I have to go.

525
01:05:29,375 --> 01:05:30,583
Sunday.

526
01:06:11,291 --> 01:06:12,541
THANA

527
01:07:43,500 --> 01:07:44,750
Why did you come here?

528
01:07:50,958 --> 01:07:53,666
I just want you to change your mind
about your resignation.

529
01:07:57,208 --> 01:07:59,000
You came to look for me...

530
01:08:01,166 --> 01:08:03,166
but you might have been another person
to die because of me.

531
01:08:03,625 --> 01:08:04,875
Another?

532
01:08:13,250 --> 01:08:15,416
You think Nok died because of you?

533
01:08:16,625 --> 01:08:17,875
Why?

534
01:08:18,041 --> 01:08:21,666
Why do you blame yourself
when it was all an accident?

535
01:08:25,958 --> 01:08:27,083
You know nothing.

536
01:08:34,875 --> 01:08:36,166
You just don't know.

537
01:08:52,458 --> 01:08:54,125
Calm down!

538
01:08:56,333 --> 01:08:58,166
Help is here. Calm down.

539
01:08:58,250 --> 01:08:59,791
Calm down.

540
01:09:51,875 --> 01:09:53,500
Do you want to wait for Dr. Suthee?

541
01:09:53,583 --> 01:09:54,791
No, I'm okay.

542
01:09:56,458 --> 01:09:58,125
Still no pulse, defib 200 joules.

543
01:10:01,958 --> 01:10:03,125
You're going to be okay, Nok.

544
01:10:07,291 --> 01:10:08,625
Nok, I can help you.

545
01:10:14,625 --> 01:10:16,791
Always together. You told me so, Nok.

546
01:10:23,458 --> 01:10:24,458
-Out.
-Doctor.

547
01:10:24,541 --> 01:10:25,958
That's enough.

548
01:10:26,125 --> 01:10:27,916
The patient is no longer with us.

549
01:10:42,500 --> 01:10:43,958
Hold the mask, hold it.

550
01:10:49,041 --> 01:10:51,166
No, I can still help her.

551
01:10:54,916 --> 01:10:55,875
No, Nok.

552
01:10:56,958 --> 01:10:58,291
Nok, wake up.

553
01:10:58,583 --> 01:10:59,875
What will I do without you?

554
01:11:00,125 --> 01:11:02,041
Doctor, she's gone.

555
01:11:03,375 --> 01:11:05,708
Come back, Nok, come back!

556
01:11:06,125 --> 01:11:07,458
Damn it!

557
01:11:09,375 --> 01:11:12,291
You can do it, Nok.
Why aren't you holding the mask?

558
01:11:13,541 --> 01:11:15,458
It's not true. Again.

559
01:11:15,541 --> 01:11:16,750
-Doctor.
-It's not true, don't do this.

560
01:11:18,083 --> 01:11:19,416
Always together, Nok.

561
01:11:19,541 --> 01:11:21,500
Always together, Nok.

562
01:11:55,833 --> 01:11:58,583
But in the end,

563
01:11:58,666 --> 01:12:00,250
there was no miracle.

564
01:12:03,291 --> 01:12:04,541
People die.

565
01:12:13,375 --> 01:12:16,916
Even though you couldn't save her,

566
01:12:17,000 --> 01:12:19,458
that doesn't mean
any other doctor could have.

567
01:12:21,958 --> 01:12:23,458
You said it yourself.

568
01:12:24,500 --> 01:12:26,000
People die.

569
01:12:30,000 --> 01:12:31,500
Nok is gone.

570
01:12:34,583 --> 01:12:37,416
I said she was dead,

571
01:12:37,500 --> 01:12:39,125
but I didn't say she was gone.

572
01:12:41,708 --> 01:12:42,875
She's still here.

573
01:12:55,041 --> 01:12:56,166
Yes.

574
01:12:57,416 --> 01:12:58,958
She's still here...

575
01:13:03,875 --> 01:13:05,625
but only in your heart.

576
01:13:16,000 --> 01:13:17,250
You don't understand.

577
01:13:21,083 --> 01:13:22,541
She really is still here.

578
01:13:39,458 --> 01:13:40,958
Nok donated her body.

579
01:13:42,375 --> 01:13:45,000
If she'd lived,
she would be a lecturing doctor.

580
01:13:46,041 --> 01:13:48,833
But even though she's not here,
her body is examined by students.

581
01:13:53,083 --> 01:13:54,291
Thana.

582
01:13:55,958 --> 01:13:57,125
I think...

583
01:14:26,291 --> 01:14:28,041
I put that there.

584
01:14:28,125 --> 01:14:32,125
I thought Nok wouldn't want me
to take it off.

585
01:14:42,500 --> 01:14:43,583
At first...

586
01:14:45,833 --> 01:14:46,958
I thought...

587
01:14:48,958 --> 01:14:51,166
I could help you get over her.

588
01:14:52,833 --> 01:14:55,041
So you can walk away from your past.

589
01:14:59,083 --> 01:15:01,375
But this is more serious than I imagined.

590
01:15:05,791 --> 01:15:07,166
Thank you

591
01:15:08,666 --> 01:15:10,333
for trying to help.

592
01:15:14,958 --> 01:15:16,791
You should stop trying, it's no use.

593
01:15:17,083 --> 01:15:18,333
No one can help me.

594
01:15:18,458 --> 01:15:20,791
Nobody can help you,
or you just don't want to be helped?

595
01:15:26,166 --> 01:15:27,000
That's right.

596
01:15:31,041 --> 01:15:32,833
Your forever love.

597
01:15:34,416 --> 01:15:36,791
It's so great that you need no help.

598
01:15:42,791 --> 01:15:44,000
As for me...

599
01:15:47,375 --> 01:15:48,458
it doesn't matter.

600
01:15:49,833 --> 01:15:51,458
I can't help myself either.

601
01:15:56,750 --> 01:15:58,541
You know that I like you, right?

602
01:16:03,083 --> 01:16:04,208
And you?

603
01:16:22,583 --> 01:16:25,333
There is only you and me
in this room, Thana.

604
01:17:16,541 --> 01:17:17,750
Help me, please.

605
01:17:20,208 --> 01:17:21,500
Help me, please.

606
01:18:16,208 --> 01:18:18,041
You were sleeping,
so I didn't want to wake you.

607
01:18:18,375 --> 01:18:21,083
The new clothes are for you.
And please lock the house. 

608
01:19:30,750 --> 01:19:31,750
Nok.

609
01:19:33,875 --> 01:19:36,458
Nok, I know that you love me.

610
01:19:43,375 --> 01:19:44,625
But please let me go.

611
01:20:46,958 --> 01:20:48,250
I'm sorry, Nok.

612
01:20:48,791 --> 01:20:50,000
I'm sorry.

613
01:21:13,041 --> 01:21:15,041
You seem to be in a good mood today.

614
01:21:15,500 --> 01:21:16,958
You think so?

615
01:21:18,750 --> 01:21:24,000
You're the second female surgeon
who hums while operating.

616
01:21:26,166 --> 01:21:27,541
Who is the first one?

617
01:21:28,208 --> 01:21:29,416
Dr. Nok.

618
01:21:32,625 --> 01:21:36,458
But Dr. Nok, she could only hum one song.

619
01:21:38,250 --> 01:21:39,666
Which song?

620
01:21:43,791 --> 01:21:45,416
I'll look for it.

621
01:21:45,750 --> 01:21:48,375
Because she always listened to it.

622
01:21:48,958 --> 01:21:53,333
Dr. Thana used to sing the song for her
in front of other people, too.

623
01:22:33,750 --> 01:22:36,416
You think Nok wants me to forget her?

624
01:22:36,500 --> 01:22:38,875
If we only try to hold on
to the happy moments,

625
01:22:38,958 --> 01:22:41,708
isn't it harder to let go of the pain?

626
01:22:52,583 --> 01:22:54,125
But Nok didn't like it.

627
01:22:54,750 --> 01:22:56,666
So I had to sneak up here a lot.

628
01:22:56,791 --> 01:22:58,500
But you still brought her along.

629
01:22:59,708 --> 01:23:00,833
You don't understand.

630
01:23:01,083 --> 01:23:02,250
She's still here.

631
01:23:02,333 --> 01:23:03,666
She's still here,

632
01:23:04,375 --> 01:23:06,541
but only in your heart.

633
01:23:06,666 --> 01:23:08,916
You should stop trying, it's no use.

634
01:23:09,125 --> 01:23:10,458
No one can help me.

635
01:23:10,583 --> 01:23:13,500
Nobody can help you,
or you just don't want to be helped?

636
01:23:32,958 --> 01:23:34,541
I have feelings for her.

637
01:23:36,166 --> 01:23:38,375
But it's not the same thing
that I feel for you.

638
01:23:39,541 --> 01:23:40,875
What should I do?

639
01:23:47,125 --> 01:23:48,750
What should I tell her?

640
01:24:05,666 --> 01:24:06,916
You already know.

641
01:24:09,166 --> 01:24:11,166
I will never leave you.

642
